################################################################################
# Install
################################################################################
Install processing

http://processing.org/


################################################################################
# Work flow
################################################################################

Here's how I work under Linux.

1) Download and untar the processing setup. This creates a directory called

processing

in which there is an executable (as well as other subdirectories) called 

processing

2) In this directory create a soft link to the shd_chicago_2012 and the 
processing_examples subdirectory.

For example, if I am in the processing directory (where the executable lives),
I would type

    ln -s ~/shd_chicago_2012/ .

3) Start processing. 
3a) From the Sketchbook IDE, open the shd_chicago_2012/processing_examples/Brownian
sketch. 
3b) Run it!
